The

These

process,
malicious

a

Faulkner

Monk v.
Ehret,
192
Cal.
186, 219
Pac.
452
(1923),

there
was
under
consideration
a
statute
similar
to
ours,
and

after
reviewing
the
history
of
the
enactment
of
such

statutes,
it
was
concluded
that
the
term
“personal
injuries”

in
the
statute
was
limited
to
corporeal
or
physical
injuries

by
reason
of
any
violence.
That
court,
in
Plum
v.
Forgay

Lumber
Co.,
118
Cal.App.
76, 4
P.2d
804

the

injury”

malicious

maintained
in
the
county

arrest

Other
courts
have
held
to

contrary.

Hatcher v.

Southern
Ry.
Co.,
191
Ala.
634,
68
So.
55

However,
we
feel
that
under
Robinson,
supra,

view

California

Ehret,

the
Faulkner

Circuit
Court

without
venue.

anything
